Effectively you are asking to have the content shrink on smaller screens. A common way for this to be achieved without needing to do a whole lot in the media query department is to use the `rem` unit, and to use CSS&#39; media queries to change the font-size property on the HTML tag, thereby updating all the other tags.

[Some Breakpoints to look at](https://medium.com/@uiuxlab/the-most-used-responsive-breakpoints-in-2017-of-mine-9588e9bd3a8a) (keep in mind, this is one dude, so do some other searches for common device breakpoints)


