Another way would be to use CSS Variables, and using the same media query trick to simply update the variable on smaller screens. This would be nice because then you could have different sizes that you update independently based on screen size for a more optimal look and feel. This does, however, carry some overhead. 

A rough example is below, but please look up [CSS Variables](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/var) a bit on your own.

    :root {
        --font-size: 16px;
    }
    
    .item { 
        font-size: var(--font-size);
    }
    
    @media (max-width: 400px) {
